Author:
Vol / Page: 3
Edition:
Quote: The shingle terraces by which these rivers are enclosed on both sides are high and abrupt towards the south, where they ascend to an altitude of about 120 feet, rising gently on the northern side and forming a shingle plain with a great deal of swampy ground, cut through by numerous smaller rivulets and creeks.
